===========================================================================
License Overview
===========================================================================

This project uses a mixed licensing model. Individual components are
licensed as follows:

  Components under AGPLv3:
    - frontend/       Lexer, parser, and AST construction
    - compiler/       Compiler backend, code generation, and optimization
    - interpreter/    Interpreter (including interpreter runtime)
    - asm/            Assembly code generation

  Components under LGPLv3:
    - runtime/        Compile-time runtime (linkable into end-user binaries)
    - stdlib/         Standard library

The full text of each license is included in the respective subdirectory.

===========================================================================
Third-Party Components
===========================================================================

This project integrates NASM (The Netwide Assembler), licensed under the
BSD 2-Clause License. See asm/THIRD_PARTY.md for copyright and license.

===========================================================================
Licensing Intent (Non-Legal)
===========================================================================

The intent of this licensing structure is:

1. The Hybrid compiler and interpreter are free software. Modifications
   to these tools, or their provision as a network service, require
   corresponding source code to be made available.

2. Programs written in the Hybrid language are independent works, not
   subject to the AGPL license of the compiler/interpreter. Users are
   free to license their own programs as they see fit.

3. The compile-time runtime and standard library use LGPL, ensuring that
   users who compile their programs into standalone executables may
   distribute them under their own terms, subject only to the LGPL
   requirements (providing library source and allowing replacement).

